          "title": "The mystery revealed and the minister sent (1:24-29)",
          "body": "Paul closes the chapter not with himself as authority but as steward. He rejoices in his sufferings *for your sake* (1:24) — not adding to Christ's atoning work (impossible) but completing the apostolic affliction the gospel costs its messengers (cf. 2 Corinthians 11:23-29). His commission (*oikonomia*, household-stewardship) is to *fully carry out the preaching of the word of God* — to announce the mystery hidden for ages and now revealed: *Christ in you, the hope of glory* (1:27). Against the false teachers' secret-society Gnosis, Paul preaches an open mystery — Gentiles included, no initiation required, the indwelling Christ Himself the guarantee of future glory. The chapter ends with the goal (1:28) — *that we may present every man complete in Christ* — and the means (1:29) — Paul's striving energized by Christ's power working within him. Divine energy and human labor in the same act."
